by billy rennekamp
billyrennekamp.com

----------------------------

To use DVDBounce just put 

 <script src="js/jquery.DVDBounce.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

in your header below your jQuery
then add

$(document).ready(function(){
  $('#DVD').DVDBounce();
});

NOTE:
you can change the increment by which the images move like below:

$(document).ready(function(){
  $('#DVD').DVDBounce({
    inc:1
  });
});


last you need to include your images in the body of your html 
these will be cycled through each time the container hits an edge
make sure you use the same div ID as inside of your jquery call

<div id="DVD">
 <img src="dvd1.png">
 <img src="dvd2.png">
 <img src="dvd3.png">
</div>

----------------------------

DVDBounce was made for everyone but with rafael rozendaal & constant dullaart in mind
they each have a special relationship to the floating dvd symbol

